2026-06-11 14:26:21,932 - INFO - Answer: The institution of Insurance Ombudsmen has been created by the Government of India under the Redressal of Public Grievances Rules, 1998. Each Ombudsman is empowered to redress customer grievances in respect of insurance contracts on personal lines where the compensation amount sought is less than Rs.30 lakhs. The Insurance Ombudsman adjudicates upon the complaint and issues an Award.
